CurrentRule.name: Set Covered Benefits - Medical includes Pres Drugs

Assign.Value: Terminal Liability Aggregate Benefit Attachment Point
The Terminal Liability Aggregate Benefit Attachment Point is equal to the sum of the Aggregate Deductible Factors for all Covered Benefits, multiplied by the greater of:
a)   The sum of the number of Covered Units for each of the last 3 Benefit Months of the Policy Year, or
b)   The average number of Covered Units for all Benefit Months in the Policy Year, multiplied by 3.
